  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bc8 \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0b9f\u0bc8 \u0b9a\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf \u0bae\u0bc1\u0ba9\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b85\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bb2\u0bcd ; \u0b95\u0b9c\u0bc7\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bca\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0ba9\u0bae\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bb2\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Threats at gunpoint to anyone who forbids the installation of a Buddha statue; Gajendrakumar Ponnambalam",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "Gajendrakumar Ponnambalam, leader of the Tamil National People's Front (TNPF) and a member of parliament, said a man who tried to block a statue of the Buddha in the Kurundur hills had been threatened at gunpoint.",
        "He made this statement at a media briefing of the Tamil National People's Front held in Jaffna on Tuesday (28).",
        "On the 13th, an attempt was made to erect a statue of the Buddha in the Kurundur hills, but the activity was stopped.",
        "In this situation, on the 15th, unidentified persons acted to threaten the protesters.",
        "The man was threatened at gunpoint by two unidentified men as he was leaving the house after completing his routine duties.",
        "The two of them went into a nearby army camp. The person who was threatened for security reasons after this issue has been displaced and living in a different area.",
        "He had lodged a complaint with the police about this and had contacted us directly and recorded these matters.",
        "Also, when he tried to lodge a complaint with the Jaffna Human Rights Commission, he was asked to register a complaint with the Human Rights Commission in Vavuniya as a person from Mullaitivu.",
        "Minister Sarath Weerasekara, who was in charge of internal security, registered the name of our party's general secretary Gajendran and threatened other Tamil factions in parliament and those seeking to protect Tamil identity and places.",
        "The government does not appear to be taking any further action in this regard. Such incidents are taking place in the context of the many stories that went to Geneva in July.",
        "He said the government was actively involved in the destruction of the Tamil nation in the current context of the country.",
        "It is noteworthy that MP Selvaraja Gajendran and the person who was threatened participated in this press conference."
      ],
